## Log More Than One Thing

You can pass **multiple items** to `console.log()` by separating them with **commas**:

```javascript
console.log("Name:", "Alice");
// Output: Name: Alice
```

JavaScript automatically adds a **space** between each item. You can mix text and numbers too:

```javascript
console.log("Age:", 25);
// Output: Age: 25
```

This is incredibly useful for **debugging** — you can label your output to know exactly what you're looking at!

slides.codeSnippet:
console.log("Line 1\nLine 2");
console.log("Name:\tAlice");
console.log("She said \"Hello!\"");
console.log("Path: C:\\Users\\Alice");
